Annotation.note:
A problem posed at International Mathematical Olympiad:
A non-isosceles triangle $A_1 A_2 A_3$ has sides $a_1$, $a_2$, $a_3$ with $a_i$ opposite to $A_i$. $M_i$ is the midpoint of the side $a_i$ and $T_i$ is the point where the incircle touches side $a_i$. Denote by $S_i$ the reflection of $T_i$ in the interior bisector of angle $A_i$. Prove that the lines $M_1 S_1$, $M_2 S_2$ and $M_3 S_3$ are concurrent.
\begin{keywords} geometry theorem proving \end{keywords}
